onstantly desire to cause arguments and quarrels between people. Many constantly desire to deceive others. Many constantly desire to speak hatefully about others. \n\n<verse number=\"30\" style=\"v\" />Many say evil things about others. Many slander others. Many act especially hatefully toward God. Many act violently toward others. Many treat others contemptuously. Many boast about themselves to others. Many invent new ways to do evil deeds. Many children disobey their parents.\n\n<verse number=\"31\" style=\"v\" />Many act in other foolish ways that offend God. Many do not do what they promised others that they would do. Many do not even love their own family members. And many do not act mercifully toward other people.\n"}, {"format": "usx", "id": "01-32", "img": "", "text": "<verse number=\"32\" style=\"v\" />Although they know that God has declared that those who do such things deserve to be killed, they not only do these kinds of evil things, but they also approve of others who do them.\n"}], "number": "01", "ref": "", "title": ""}, {"frames": [{"format": "usx", "id": "02-01", "img": "", "text": "<verse number=\"1\" style=\"v\" />God will severely punish people who habitually do evil deeds, because he has clearly revealed that he is angry with them. So when God judges people, he will not excuse any one of you, my Jewish friends. You say that God should punish non-Jews for doing evil deeds. But when any one of you says that, you are really saying that God should punish yourself, because you do some of the same evil deeds  that the non-Jews do. \n\n<verse number=\"2\" style=\"v\" />We know very well that God will judge and punish fairly non-Jewish people who do such evil deeds. \n"}, {"format": "usx", "id": "02-03", "img": "", "text": "<verse number=\"3\" style=\"v\" />So you who say God should punish others for doing evil deeds although you do evil deeds yourself, you should certainly not think that you yourself will be able to escape from God, when he begins to 